learning_outcomes.en:
The student: 
- knows the environments and methods of youth work;
- defines suitable methods to meet young people's needs and goals;
- analyses the risks associated with ensuring a safe environment;
- explains the basics of preparing a risk analysis;
- implements methods of self-analysis, incl.  working with young people;
- understands legislation and guidance on health and safety at work with children and young people, and the need to ensure a safe physical and mental environment;
- describes a response in emergency situations, incl. other youth workers' support in creating a safe environment and monitoring safety requirements.
